# Privacy and Data

## Never commit or expose

- Real customer data, contacts, pricing, supplier records, or internal documents
- API keys, tokens, passwords, or service-role credentials
- Private data in screenshots, logs, QA reports, fixtures, or prompts

## Fixtures and local data

- Git-tracked fixtures must be synthetic and customer-neutral.
- Local customer inputs belong under ignored paths (see `scripts/data-preparation/local/`).
- Use `.env.local` for secrets; only placeholders in `.env.example`.

## QA and monitoring

- Redact or omit sensitive fields in findings.
- Do not paste `.env` values into chat or reports.

## Reference

Follow `docs/engineering/agent-privacy-policy.md` and `AGENTS.md` §7–8.
